 31s ARGUMENTS
 31s         void
 31s 
 31s DESCRIPTION
 31s        This  function initializes the OATH library.  Every user of this library needs to
 31s        call this function before using other functions.   You  should  call  oath_done()
 31s        when use of the OATH library is no longer needed.
 31s 
 31s        Note  that  this  function  may also initialize Libgcrypt, if the OATH library is
 31s        built with libgcrypt support and libgcrypt has not been initialized before.  Thus
 31s        if  you  want to manually initialize libgcrypt you must do it before calling this
 31s        function.  This is useful in cases you want to disable libgcrypt's internal lock‐
 31s        ings etc.
 31s 
 31s RETURNS
 31s        On success, OATH_OK (zero) is returned, otherwise an error code is returned.
